natural problem: In parallelogram $ABCD$, angle $B$ measures $110^\circ$. What is the number of degrees in the measure of angle $C$?
natural solution: [asy] unitsize(1inch); pair A,B,C,D; B = (0,0); C = (1,0); A = rotate(100)*(0.6,0); D = A+C; draw(A--B--C--D--A); label("$A$",A,N); label("$D$",D,N); label("$B$",B,S); label("$C$",C,S); [/asy] Because $\overline{AB}\parallel\overline{CD}$, we have $\angle B + \angle C = 180^\circ$.
